*** REQUIRED EXISTING-FILE CHANGES FOR FULL SMARTLOG STORAGE ***

This ZIP contains only new files as requested.
For full production storage in app.jsonl + issue-current.jsonl + error.jsonl,
wire the new Rust module into the existing Tauri command list.

1) In src-tauri/src/core.rs near other module declarations, add:

mod smart_log;

2) In tauri::generate_handler![ ... ], add:

smart_log::smart_log_write,
smart_log::smart_log_read_last,
smart_log::smart_log_clear,
smart_log::smart_log_dir,
smart_log::smart_log_rotate,

3) Optional after migration:
- Keep existing log_write/log_read_last for compatibility.
- New frontend SmartLog first tries smart_log_write.
- If smart_log_write is not registered yet, it falls back to current log_write/app.jsonl.

4) Do not add every new event id to old LOG_IDS.
SmartLog v1 stores its own id inside the JSON row and does not need old LOG_IDS.
